1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:01,793
<i><b>Alice?</b></i>

2
00:00:01,876 --> 00:00:05,755
<i><b>Auntie Cristina is pointing</b></i>
<i><b>at something. But I don't know what it is.</b></i>

3
00:00:05,839 --> 00:00:08,591
<i><b>Auntie is like that.</b></i>
<i><b>I often don't get her either.</b></i>

4
00:00:10,802 --> 00:00:13,847
<i><b>Althea, come on, dear! Hang on tight!</b></i>

5
00:00:13,930 --> 00:00:17,142
<i><b>This shouldn't have happened!</b></i>
<i><b>She shouldn't be around me!</b></i>

6
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:19,144
<b>[Edong] </b><i><b>You did this! No!</b></i>

7
00:00:19,227 --> 00:00:22,355
<i><b>I know your story, Edong.</b></i>
<i><b>The girls are very close to me.</b></i>

8
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:25,525
<i><b>It'll be easier if we work together.</b></i>

9
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:26,568
<i><b>-You're better off dead.</b></i>
<b>-[thwack]</b>

10
00:00:26,651 --> 00:00:27,777
<b>[grunts] </b><i><b>Don't! Agh!</b></i>

11
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:30,155
<i><b>Your dad is back here in Amurao.</b></i>

12
00:00:30,238 --> 00:00:32,741
<i><b>You need something from me.</b></i>
<i><b>What's in it for me, Attorney?</b></i>

13
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:34,868
<i><b>Your cooperation in catching Edong.</b></i>

14
00:00:37,245 --> 00:00:44,210
<b>[theme music playing]</b>

15
00:01:52,737 --> 00:01:54,155
<b>What?</b>

16
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:58,284
<b>You'll use me as bait</b>
<b>to catch that crazy man?</b>

17
00:01:58,868 --> 00:02:00,703
<b>He's out of his mind.</b>

18
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,372
<b>When he sees me,</b>

19
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:05,750
<b>he'll come at me and</b>
<b>do what I did to his mother.</b>

20
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:08,294
<b>Everything will be under control.</b>

21
00:02:08,378 --> 00:02:10,380
<b>The cops will be securing the location.</b>

22
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:13,424
<b>We'll make sure that you are safe.</b>

23
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:17,762
<b>[pensive music playing]</b>

24
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:19,139
<b>I'm not a fool.</b>

25
00:02:21,724 --> 00:02:24,060
<b>You had two accomplices</b>
<b>in the robbery and homicide.</b>

26
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:26,563
<b>-Both of them are free.</b>
<b>-[Crisanto breathes deeply]</b>

27
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:29,190
<b>Unlucky for you,</b>
<b>it seems like you'll die in prison.</b>

28
00:02:30,608 --> 00:02:32,193
<b>You can be a witness.</b>

29
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:34,362
<b>You'll testify against both of them.</b>

30
00:02:34,445 --> 00:02:36,406
<b>If you do that,</b>

31
00:02:36,489 --> 00:02:38,616
<b>we can recommend a plea bargain</b>

32
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,202
<b>to reduce your penalty.</b>

33
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:44,873
<b>But the final say lies</b>
<b>with the prosecutor and judge.</b>

34
00:02:46,749 --> 00:02:48,126
<b>[tongue clicks]</b>

35
00:02:48,209 --> 00:02:50,295
<b>What about my case here?</b>

36
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:54,048
<b>If your testimony is</b>
<b>strong and substantial,</b>

37
00:02:54,924 --> 00:02:57,051
<b>we can present it as cooperation.</b>

38
00:02:57,594 --> 00:03:00,555
<b>That can help reduce your sentence.</b>

39
00:03:00,638 --> 00:03:01,681
<b>It won't go away.</b>

40
00:03:02,932 --> 00:03:04,058
<b>But it can be reduced.</b>

41
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:11,024
<b>[music becomes suspenseful]</b>

42
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:14,277
<b>Is that for sure?</b>

43
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:18,114
<b>There's no guarantee for a grave case.</b>

44
00:03:18,197 --> 00:03:21,034
<b>Again, the prosecutor and judge</b>
<b>make the decision.</b>

45
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:23,119
<b>But if I'm your lawyer,</b>

46
00:03:23,202 --> 00:03:24,662
<b>you'd have a strong case.</b>

47
00:03:26,122 --> 00:03:29,250
<b>You agreed to what she's saying?</b>

48
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:37,217
<b>[suspenseful music crescendos]</b>

49
00:03:37,884 --> 00:03:38,843
<b>[Marco] </b><i><b>Are you sure about this?</b></i>

50
00:03:39,802 --> 00:03:43,765
<i><b>You don't defend</b></i>
<i><b>people like Crisanto Santiago!</b></i>

51
00:03:43,848 --> 00:03:46,517
<i><b>Whether we like it or not,</b></i>
<i><b>this is our reality now!</b></i>

52
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:49,520
<i><b>We need him to get Edong out of hiding!</b></i>

53
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:50,855
<b>[tense music playing]</b>

54
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:52,273
<i><b>You said it yourself, Lucas.</b></i>

55
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:55,652
<i><b>Everything that's</b></i>
<i><b>happening now is because of him.</b></i>

56
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:57,278
<i><b>Because he killed your mother.</b></i>

57
00:03:57,946 --> 00:04:01,115
<i><b>That's how mad he is at Edong!</b></i>
<i><b>We can use that!</b></i>

58
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:02,450
<i><b>In exchange for what?</b></i>

59
00:04:03,493 --> 00:04:04,577
<i><b>Leniency?</b></i>

60
00:04:05,495 --> 00:04:06,829
<i><b>Plea bargain?</b></i>

61
00:04:07,538 --> 00:04:09,707
<i><b>Erica, he killed my mother!</b></i>

62
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:12,752
<i><b>Edong will kill more</b></i>
<i><b>people if we don't do this!</b></i>

63
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:14,295
<b>[tense music continues]</b>

64
00:04:14,379 --> 00:04:16,673
<i><b>My sister's in</b></i>
<i><b>the hospital, fighting for her life!</b></i>

65
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:18,341
<b>[music becomes somber]</b>

66
00:04:18,424 --> 00:04:19,926
<i><b>Who's next?</b></i>

67
00:04:20,009 --> 00:04:21,010
<i><b>Huh?</b></i>

68
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:24,597
<i><b>How many people need to be hurt or die?</b></i>

69
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:28,851
<i><b>You know I'm right, Lucas.</b></i>

70
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:34,857
<i><b>So if you want to save what's left of your</b></i>
<i><b>brother's soul, we must do this!</b></i>

71
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:36,859
<b>[somber music continues]</b>

72
00:04:38,403 --> 00:04:40,113
<b>If the death penalty still existed,</b>

73
00:04:40,196 --> 00:04:43,700
<b>I'd demand</b>
<b>it a hundred times over for you!</b>

74
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:46,995
<b>-[scoffs]</b>
<b>-I'm just doing this for my brother!</b>

75
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:48,788
<b>[chuckles sarcastically]</b>

76
00:04:48,871 --> 00:04:50,373
<b>[sighing deeply]</b>

77
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:53,334
<b>Your brother is insane.</b>

78
00:04:53,876 --> 00:04:54,919
<b>He's crazy!</b>

79
00:04:55,712 --> 00:04:56,754
<b>[Erica] Lucas!</b>

80
00:04:57,672 --> 00:05:00,425
<b>-Say that again.</b>
<b>-Not In my station, Mr. Santiago!</b>

81
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:03,761
<b>No personal vendettas!</b>

82
00:05:04,929 --> 00:05:06,347
<b>No vigilante justice!</b>

83
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:08,182
<b>Otherwise, let's just end this!</b>

84
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:14,397
<b>[tense music resumes]</b>

85
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,565
<b>Fine.</b>

86
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:19,068
<b>Let's do it.</b>

87
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:23,156
<b>But you have to keep your word, Attorney.</b>

88
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:29,370
<b>[music turns ominous]</b>

89
00:05:31,873 --> 00:05:34,709
<b>[Lucas] All of this would be for nothing</b>
<b>if he doesn't read my message.</b>

90
00:05:34,792 --> 00:05:36,002
<b>"EDONG, I CAUGHT PAPA AT OUR OLD HOUSE.</b>

91
00:05:36,085 --> 00:05:37,211
<b>HE'S NOW BEING DETAINED."</b>

92
00:05:37,295 --> 00:05:39,547
<b>I keep texting and calling him,</b>
<b>but he's not responding.</b>

93
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:41,549
<b>He probably changes his number often.</b>

94
00:05:42,341 --> 00:05:43,593
<b>[Marco] He can't be traced.</b>

95
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:48,806
<b>There's nothing we can do but wait</b>
<b>and hope he reads your message.</b>

96
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:52,727
<b>Hopefully,</b>
<b>it'll trigger him enough to show up.</b>

97
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:59,734
<b>[stirring music playing]</b>

98
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:09,744
<b>[Marco breathing deeply]</b>

99
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:14,123
<b>[footsteps receding]</b>

100
00:06:18,544 --> 00:06:20,004
<b>[music ends]</b>

101
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:21,756
<b>[huffs]</b>

102
00:06:21,839 --> 00:06:23,841
<b>[uneasy music playing]</b>

103
00:06:23,925 --> 00:06:25,009
<b>[exhales heavily]</b>

104
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:29,430
<b>[sighs exasperatedly]</b>

105
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:38,689
<b>[phone ringing]</b>

106
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:40,942
<b>[uneasy music continues]</b>

107
00:06:41,025 --> 00:06:42,151
<b>Hello?</b>

108
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:44,529
<b>I knew it. You're still awake.</b>

109
00:06:44,612 --> 00:06:46,072
<b>You can't sleep as well?</b>

110
00:06:46,864 --> 00:06:49,158
<b>I can't stop thinking about Althea.</b>

111
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:53,830
<b>I just talked to</b>
<b>her the other day, and then…</b>

112
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:56,082
<b>My goodness.</b>

113
00:06:56,582 --> 00:06:58,126
<b>I wonder how she's doing.</b>

114
00:06:59,043 --> 00:07:00,962
<b>Do you think she'll survive?</b>

115
00:07:01,462 --> 00:07:05,508
<b>[sighs] Oh God,</b>
<b>there's so much death. I…</b>

116
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:08,761
<b>It's like a shadow</b>
<b>that just won't leave me alone.</b>

117
00:07:09,637 --> 00:07:11,180
<b>First, my dad.</b>

118
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:12,348
<b>Louisa.</b>

119
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:14,809
<i><b>Now… Althea.</b></i>

120
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:18,062
<b>That entrapment plan for Edong…</b>

121
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,731
<b>I don't feel good about it.</b>

122
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:23,943
<b>Even with the police,</b>
<b>it's still dangerous.</b>

123
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:25,153
<b>[breathes deeply]</b>

124
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:27,780
<b>I really wish it would all end soon.</b>

125
00:07:28,656 --> 00:07:30,783
<i><b>Will it ever be over?</b></i>

126
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,827
<b>Even if Edong is caught,</b>

127
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:36,038
<b>if he isn't really the one who killed</b>
<b>Louisa, then that means…</b>

128
00:07:36,747 --> 00:07:38,291
<b>the killer is still out there.</b>

129
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,251
<b>The killer is still free.</b>

130
00:07:40,334 --> 00:07:43,713
<b>[uneasy music continues, fades]</b>

131
00:07:43,796 --> 00:07:45,089
<b>Erica.</b>

132
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:49,510
<b>I was hoping to ask a favor.</b>

133
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:55,516
<b>Don't let my brother die.</b>

134
00:07:59,353 --> 00:08:01,397
<b>I know he has killed a lot of people.</b>

135
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:03,483
<b>He hurt them.</b>

136
00:08:04,358 --> 00:08:06,110
<b>One of them being your sister.</b>

137
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:11,199
<b>But he's still my brother.</b>

138
00:08:13,659 --> 00:08:15,495
<b>I can't give up on him.</b>

139
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:18,247
<b>[melancholic music playing]</b>

140
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:19,916
<b>I'll get him,</b>

141
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:21,542
<b>professional help…</b>

142
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:24,170
<b>therapy…</b>

143
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:26,172
<b>Rehab.</b>

144
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:28,966
<b>[sobs] Just to…</b>

145
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:33,638
<b>bring him back to normal.</b>

146
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:36,599
<b>To give him a chance.</b>

147
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:40,937
<b>One that he was never given.</b>

148
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:44,524
<b>Because… [cries softly]</b>

149
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:47,527
<b>[melancholic music continues]</b>

150
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:50,780
<b>Because from the very beginning,</b>
<b>the odds have been stacked against him.</b>

151
00:08:57,328 --> 00:08:59,372
<b>I know he's just a victim.</b>

152
00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:01,958
<b>Just like all of us.</b>

153
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:06,254
<b>We're victims of</b>
<b>a broken and corrupt system.</b>

154
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:12,009
<b>He has to pay for everything he did.</b>

155
00:09:13,302 --> 00:09:14,804
<b>But, like you,</b>

156
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:17,932
<b>I don't want your brother to die either.</b>

157
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:21,602
<b>What I want, not only for him</b>

158
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:24,230
<b>but also for all of us,</b>

159
00:09:25,273 --> 00:09:29,318
<b>this is a chance, to start again.</b>

160
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,862
<b>A chance to fix all the damage</b>

161
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:34,073
<b>caused by one mistake.</b>

162
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:43,833
<b>[tender music playing]</b>

163
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:50,756
<b>Thank you.</b>

164
00:09:57,722 --> 00:10:02,059
<b>[tender music continues]</b>

165
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:05,313
<b>-[phone ringing]</b>
<b>-[music fades]</b>

166
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:09,525
<b>[ringing continues]</b>

167
00:10:10,401 --> 00:10:11,611
<b>Hello, Edong?</b>

168
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:15,781
<b>Why didn't you tell me?</b>

169
00:10:16,699 --> 00:10:18,701
<b>Why did you take him to the police?</b>

170
00:10:18,784 --> 00:10:20,745
<b>You should have brought him to me.</b>

171
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:21,996
<b>Exactly how, Edong?</b>

172
00:10:22,079 --> 00:10:23,539
<b>I don't know how to contact you.</b>

173
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,958
<b>I don't know where you are.</b>
<b>How was I supposed to do that?</b>

174
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:28,044
<i><b>You should have waited for me.</b></i>

175
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:31,297
<b>It was supposed to be</b>
<b>the two of us, remember?</b>

176
00:10:32,089 --> 00:10:34,216
<b>Edong, I didn't plan this.</b>

177
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,677
<b>I didn't know I would see him there.</b>

178
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:37,887
<b>[sucks teeth]</b>

179
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:41,307
<b>It is not the police</b>
<b>who will make him pay.</b>

180
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,809
<b>-[ominous music playing]</b>
<b>-It will be me.</b>

181
00:10:45,269 --> 00:10:46,812
<b>Me alone.</b>

182
00:10:48,439 --> 00:10:50,775
<i><b>He wronged the both of us.</b></i>

183
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:53,736
<b>He killed our mother.</b>

184
00:10:54,695 --> 00:10:58,699
<b>It is only right</b>
<b>that we deliver justice ourselves.</b>

185
00:10:58,783 --> 00:11:03,454
<b>[ominous music continues]</b>

186
00:11:03,537 --> 00:11:06,082
<b>I want that when I see out mother again.</b>

187
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:09,543
<i><b>To have something to</b></i>
<i><b>be proud of in front of her.</b></i>

188
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:12,546
<b>That I avenged her.</b>

189
00:11:15,549 --> 00:11:17,385
<b>[sighs] You're right, Edong.</b>

190
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:20,388
<b>We're the ones who should make them pay.</b>

191
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:24,809
<b>I was wrong to bring him to the police.</b>

192
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:30,106
<b>But I know how to get him back.</b>

193
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:35,736
<b>How?</b>

194
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:40,616
<b>He has another case in Cavite.</b>

195
00:11:41,867 --> 00:11:43,244
<b>The hearing for that will come first.</b>

196
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:45,454
<b>He'll be transferred there tomorrow.</b>

197
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:47,706
<b>Transferred?</b>

198
00:11:48,082 --> 00:11:51,377
<b>He can't leave Amurao.</b>

199
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:52,837
<b>Exactly, Edong.</b>

200
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:55,923
<b>This is our chance to get him back.</b>

201
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:57,800
<b>A police van,</b>

202
00:11:58,551 --> 00:12:00,386
<b>will take him there tomorrow.</b>

203
00:12:01,137 --> 00:12:02,805
<b>That's where we can take him back.</b>

204
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:05,474
<b>Will you help me?</b>

205
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:08,602
<b>Yes, Edong.</b>

206
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,648
<b>Looks like you've finally</b>
<b>come to your senses, bro?</b>

207
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:19,697
<b>Maybe Attorney will cry in anger</b>
<b>when she hears what you're saying.</b>

208
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:23,576
<i><b>Stay away from that woman, bro.</b></i>

209
00:12:23,659 --> 00:12:27,371
<b>[exhales] And her friends too.</b>
<b>They're demons.</b>

210
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,373
<i><b>Alice…</b></i>

211
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:31,083
<i><b>Beth…</b></i>

212
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:32,751
<b>Mel…</b>

213
00:12:33,377 --> 00:12:34,962
<b>Crisanto…</b>

214
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:36,422
<i><b>…and Erica.</b></i>

215
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:39,925
<i><b>Tomorrow I'll show you,</b></i>

216
00:12:40,676 --> 00:12:43,679
<b>how we can finally be free from them.</b>

217
00:12:43,762 --> 00:12:47,308
<b>[music becomes foreboding]</b>

218
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:48,601
<b>Okay, Edong.</b>

219
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:52,813
<b>Tomorrow, at six in the evening,</b>

220
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:56,025
<b>the van will leave</b>
<b>the police station in Amurao.</b>

221
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:58,486
<b>Let's meet there.</b>

222
00:12:58,569 --> 00:13:00,529
<b>[ominous music sting]</b>

223
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:05,993
<b>[foreboding music continues]</b>

224
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:15,711
<b>[Chloe] Ma, Althea was</b>
<b>found on a different street, right?</b>

225
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:16,837
<b>[Beth] Mm-mm.</b>

226
00:13:17,838 --> 00:13:19,715
<b>Uncle Edward said</b>

227
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:21,175
<b>that when he arrived at their house,</b>

228
00:13:21,258 --> 00:13:23,052
<b>Althea and the police were already gone.</b>

229
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:24,011
<b>[chair slides]</b>

230
00:13:24,094 --> 00:13:27,598
<b>Because there was</b>
<b>a problem with the replacement guard?</b>

231
00:13:27,681 --> 00:13:31,310
<b>Yes. They said they were already on their</b>
<b>way to Uncle Edward's house,</b>

232
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:34,355
<b>but he stopped to help at an accident.</b>

233
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:39,485
<b>They didn't expect the first guard</b>
<b>to leave before they arrived.</b>

234
00:13:39,568 --> 00:13:44,448
<b>So the house was left without protection.</b>
<b>Then Edong happened to see Althea.</b>

235
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:49,078
<b>But what I don't understand is this,</b>

236
00:13:49,161 --> 00:13:53,207
<b>Althea's father said Althea messaged him.</b>

237
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:56,794
<b>She asked him to pick her up,</b>
<b>but not at the house, at the corner.</b>

238
00:13:57,336 --> 00:14:00,256
<b>Wait, Ma, I thought…</b>

239
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:02,258
<b>Edong attacked her inside the house?</b>

240
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:07,012
<b>So that means Althea went outside,</b>

241
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:09,098
<b>and that's where Edong saw her?</b>

242
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:12,393
<b>But Uncle Edward wasn't there,</b>
<b>and neither were the police.</b>

243
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:15,813
<b>It's impossible that Althea</b>
<b>would leave Auntie Christina alone.</b>

244
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:19,441
<b>Exactly, Ma. That's suspicious, right?</b>

245
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:21,944
<b>Hmm… Something really feels off.</b>

246
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:25,072
<b>My investigative</b>
<b>reporters are at it again.</b>

247
00:14:25,155 --> 00:14:27,658
<b>You have so many questions.</b>
<b>Maybe the answer is simple.</b>

248
00:14:28,325 --> 00:14:31,036
<b>Edong saw Althea at the house,</b>

249
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:33,747
<b>dragged her, then left her at the lot.</b>

250
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:36,417
<b>[tongue clicks] It's the message</b>
<b>to her father that feels wrong.</b>

251
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:39,336
<b>Pa, the text she sent to</b>
<b>her father is what's suspicious.</b>

252
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:41,755
<b>-Oh!</b>
<b>-Okay, okay, sorry!</b>

253
00:14:41,839 --> 00:14:43,424
<b>I don't know, you two are the smart ones.</b>

254
00:14:43,507 --> 00:14:45,259
<b>-[laughing]</b>
<b>-I told you so.</b>

255
00:14:45,342 --> 00:14:46,886
<b>[Ryan] Chloe, look--</b>

256
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:51,181
<b>Oh! So the lying</b>
<b>couple who went to jail are here.</b>

257
00:14:51,265 --> 00:14:53,976
<b>Oh! They're even laughing. So happy!</b>

258
00:14:54,059 --> 00:14:55,811
<b>Aren't they ashamed?</b>

259
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:57,229
<b>Unbelievable!</b>

260
00:14:57,813 --> 00:15:01,025
<b>Ma'am Beth acting</b>
<b>all feisty when she's a liar.</b>

261
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:03,027
<b>Hey! She might hear you.</b>

262
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:09,325
<b>-Love--</b>
<b>-It's okay.</b>

263
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:15,372
<b>Vivian, let me correct you.</b>

264
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:19,001
<b>My husband went to jail,</b>
<b>but he wasn't charged.</b>

265
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:21,420
<b>And isn't Ryan your cousin?</b>

266
00:15:21,962 --> 00:15:24,256
<b>If you're angry at me,</b>
<b>then direct it at me.</b>

267
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:26,884
<b>Don't drag him into it.</b>
<b>That's all I'm asking.</b>

268
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:32,348
<b>Okay, if you want to throw</b>
<b>unlimited shade at me, go ahead.</b>

269
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:34,099
<b>I deserve all of that.</b>

270
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:35,392
<b>Mm-mm.</b>

271
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:37,770
<b>I already said</b>
<b>everything at the press conference.</b>

272
00:15:37,853 --> 00:15:40,314
<b>Everything I'm ashamed of,</b>
<b>everything I was hiding.</b>

273
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:42,775
<b>Because I want to change.</b>

274
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:45,319
<b>Even if many people judge me,</b>

275
00:15:45,903 --> 00:15:47,738
<b>at least I feel lighter.</b>

276
00:15:48,364 --> 00:15:50,532
<b>So you know what? My suggestion to you is</b>

277
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:52,409
<b>to learn from what happened to me.</b>

278
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:54,787
<b>Because we both know</b>

279
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:57,790
<b>there are things</b>
<b>you need to take accountability for.</b>

280
00:15:57,873 --> 00:15:59,375
<b>-[scoffs]</b>
<b>-Like…</b>

281
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:03,170
<b>spreading the scandalous</b>
<b>video of your boyfriend's ex.</b>

282
00:16:03,545 --> 00:16:05,339
<b>Because you couldn't let go.</b>

283
00:16:05,422 --> 00:16:06,799
<b>Weren't you the one responsible for that?</b>

284
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:09,677
<b>Let's just go!</b>

285
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:15,099
<b>Love, what happened to her?</b>
<b>I talked to her nicely.</b>

286
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:17,351
<b>Love, I don't know if</b>
<b>you're really kind now</b>

287
00:16:17,434 --> 00:16:19,395
<b>or if you're just messing</b>
<b>with me and your daughter.</b>

288
00:16:19,478 --> 00:16:20,479
<b>-Hey, that's harsh!</b>
<b>-[chuckles]</b>

289
00:16:20,562 --> 00:16:21,730
<b>I really changed</b>

290
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:23,148
<b>-and it's still wrong?</b>
<b>-Really?</b>

291
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:24,525
<b>-[chuckles]</b>
<b>-Oh, come on.</b>

292
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:27,987
<b>-[teasing] You're so kind.</b>
<b>-Aren't I nice now?</b>

293
00:16:28,612 --> 00:16:30,364
<b>-[sighs]</b>
<b>-[car doors close]</b>

294
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:35,244
<b>[Beth] </b><i><b>That text Althea</b></i>
<i><b>sent to her dad is suspicious, right?</b></i>

295
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:38,497
<b>Yeah, but,</b>

296
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:41,083
<b>maybe she thought</b>
<b>Uncle Edward was already on his way back,</b>

297
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:42,584
<b>so she texted her dad.</b>

298
00:16:43,627 --> 00:16:45,921
<b>Then Edong arrived?</b>

299
00:16:46,588 --> 00:16:47,798
<b>Possible.</b>

300
00:16:48,590 --> 00:16:50,467
<b>What about you, Alice? What do you think?</b>

301
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:52,553
<b>Honestly…</b>

302
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:54,304
<b>I don't know.</b>

303
00:16:55,139 --> 00:16:57,349
<b>But you're right. Something feels off.</b>

304
00:16:57,975 --> 00:16:59,643
<b>I haven't been at ease since last night.</b>

305
00:17:00,102 --> 00:17:02,146
<b>[Alice] </b><i><b>I'm actually</b></i>
<i><b>going to Uncle's place.</b></i>

306
00:17:02,229 --> 00:17:05,691
<b>I've been trying to convince him</b>
<b>to just stay here with Auntie Christina.</b>

307
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:07,693
<b>I don't want them</b>
<b>staying at their house anymore.</b>

308
00:17:07,776 --> 00:17:09,486
<b>But he's being so stubborn.</b>

309
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:14,408
<b>Even my suggestion that they stay with</b>
<b>Auntie Christina's cousin, he refused.</b>

310
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:17,536
<b>But he did say Auntie gets disoriented</b>

311
00:17:17,619 --> 00:17:19,246
<i><b>when she's taken away from their house.</b></i>

312
00:17:19,913 --> 00:17:21,999
<b>So, I kind of get it.</b>

313
00:17:22,082 --> 00:17:25,335
<b>Yes. But the situation is different now.</b>

314
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:29,923
<b>They've already been breached twice</b>
<b>and someone got hurt.</b>

315
00:17:30,007 --> 00:17:32,342
<b>Him, Althea, Seth.</b>

316
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:35,929
<b>Isn't that enough proof</b>
<b>that it's not safe there anymore?</b>

317
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:42,144
<b>[unsettling music playing]</b>

318
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:44,063
<b>[Marco] Do you really</b>
<b>think Edong will come here</b>

319
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:46,940
<b>-that easily?</b>
<b>-[music fades]</b>

320
00:17:47,024 --> 00:17:49,068
<b>Won't he think this is entrapment?</b>

321
00:17:50,944 --> 00:17:53,447
<b>Hopefully,</b>
<b>his irrational and unstable behavior,</b>

322
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:56,075
<b>especially regarding his father,</b>
<b>will make him careless.</b>

323
00:17:58,202 --> 00:18:01,705
<b>The police will escort</b>
<b>you when you get into the van.</b>

324
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:02,956
<b>That's it.</b>

325
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,833
<b>That's all we need from you.</b>

326
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:06,835
<b>Try to do anything,</b>

327
00:18:07,419 --> 00:18:09,713
<b>and we won't hesitate to shoot you.</b>

328
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:14,051
<b>Remember, we have a deal.</b>

329
00:18:15,385 --> 00:18:16,762
<b>If you don't do your part,</b>

330
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:18,263
<b>I won't be able to help you either.</b>

331
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,224
<b>Just relax!</b>

332
00:18:20,974 --> 00:18:22,101
<b>Didn't you say</b>

333
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:24,895
<b>there's a chance my</b>
<b>sentence could be reduced?</b>

334
00:18:25,479 --> 00:18:27,022
<b>Why would I ruin that?</b>

335
00:18:27,981 --> 00:18:28,941
<b>For what?</b>

336
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:32,194
<b>To warn Edong about your plans?</b>

337
00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:33,237
<b>Is that it?</b>

338
00:18:34,404 --> 00:18:37,241
<b>[scoffs] I'm not Lucas.</b>

339
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:40,869
<b>Your brother…</b>

340
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:42,621
<b>has no more chance to change.</b>

341
00:18:42,704 --> 00:18:44,623
<b>-[tense music sting]</b>
<b>-You bastard!</b>

342
00:18:44,706 --> 00:18:45,874
<b>What?!</b>

343
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:48,001
<b>Enough talking!</b>

344
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:49,253
<b>Get ready!</b>

345
00:18:50,462 --> 00:18:52,256
<b>[exhales deeply]</b>

346
00:18:52,339 --> 00:18:57,219
<b>[tense music playing]</b>

347
00:18:57,302 --> 00:18:59,179
<b>Here's Althea's text.</b>

348
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:02,432
<b>Maybe you can send it to me?</b>

349
00:19:02,516 --> 00:19:04,017
<b>Sure, sure. I'll just send it to you.</b>

350
00:19:04,351 --> 00:19:05,394
<b>Thank you.</b>

351
00:19:07,563 --> 00:19:09,565
<b>We don't need to leave!</b>

352
00:19:09,648 --> 00:19:12,151
<b>Do you really think</b>
<b>that Edong will come back here?!</b>

353
00:19:12,734 --> 00:19:16,738
<b>That's what we thought after he attacked</b>
<b>Seth, but look what happened?!</b>

354
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:19,658
<b>[snickers] Alice,</b>
<b>he'll be too scared to come back here.</b>

355
00:19:19,741 --> 00:19:21,577
<b>After what happened to Althea?</b>

356
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:24,037
<b>The police will be even more alert.</b>

357
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:25,164
<b>[sighs]</b>

358
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:27,207
<b>We're fine here, okay?</b>

359
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:29,501
<b>Why are you so stubborn, uncle?!</b>

360
00:19:29,585 --> 00:19:31,420
<b>What if something happens to you?!</b>

361
00:19:31,837 --> 00:19:33,839
<b>I already lost my father!</b>

362
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:38,343
<b>-[sighs]</b>
<b>-Come on, Alice.</b>

363
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,512
<b>Don't think like that.</b>

364
00:19:40,929 --> 00:19:42,931
<b>Nothing bad will happen to me.</b>

365
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:44,516
<b>[exhales]</b>

366
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:47,936
<b>[pensive music playing]</b>

367
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:49,021
<b>[sighs]</b>

368
00:19:49,813 --> 00:19:52,566
<b>But fine, fine, fine, I'll think about it.</b>

369
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:57,154
<b>But you know your Uncle Edward, right?</b>

370
00:19:57,863 --> 00:20:00,949
<b>It's hard for me to leave</b>
<b>once I've grown attached to a house.</b>

371
00:20:01,408 --> 00:20:03,493
<b>[chuckles softly] Like when…</b>

372
00:20:04,578 --> 00:20:06,914
<b>we left that big house,</b>

373
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:10,709
<b>and when we also left…</b>

374
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:13,045
<b>my father's house.</b>

375
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:21,053
<b>[unsettling music playing]</b>

376
00:20:21,136 --> 00:20:23,889
<b>Was I ever at that house?</b>

377
00:20:26,683 --> 00:20:27,643
<b>Huh?</b>

378
00:20:29,686 --> 00:20:30,687
<b>No.</b>

379
00:20:31,813 --> 00:20:33,482
<b>Y-You never saw that house.</b>

380
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:41,156
<b>Stay here for a while, okay?</b>
<b>Watch over your Auntie Christina.</b>

381
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,699
<b>I just need to get something.</b>

382
00:20:44,493 --> 00:20:45,369
<b>Okay.</b>

383
00:20:47,162 --> 00:20:48,247
<b>[sighs sharply]</b>

384
00:20:49,998 --> 00:20:54,253
<b>-[phone ringing]</b>
<b>-[music fades]</b>

385
00:20:56,338 --> 00:20:57,214
<b>Mel?</b>

386
00:20:57,714 --> 00:21:00,884
<b>I'm really bothered by</b>
<b>what Beth said about Althea's text.</b>

387
00:21:01,635 --> 00:21:04,096
<b>So I talked to her dad.</b>

388
00:21:05,055 --> 00:21:06,640
<i><b>I asked him to send the message to me.</b></i>

389
00:21:07,182 --> 00:21:08,558
<b>Wait, I'll send it to you.</b>

390
00:21:08,642 --> 00:21:11,186
<b>[foreboding music swells]</b>

391
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:12,521
<b>[phone chimes]</b>

392
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:16,400
<b>"PA, JUST PICK ME UP AT THE CORNER.</b>

393
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:18,777
<b>BY THE SHED OVER. </b><i><b>THERE</b></i><b>"</b>

394
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:21,238
<b>Did you see it?</b>

395
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:23,407
<b>I just saw it.</b>

396
00:21:23,865 --> 00:21:24,950
<b>[Mel] </b><i><b>There…</b></i>

397
00:21:25,325 --> 00:21:27,452
<b>isn't the last word typed differently?</b>

398
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:29,705
<i><b>Aside from being in all capital letters,</b></i>

399
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:30,956
<i><b>there are no punctuations.</b></i>

400
00:21:31,039 --> 00:21:33,083
<i><b>It's not like the previous sentences.</b></i>

401
00:21:33,166 --> 00:21:34,835
<b>So, what does that mean?</b>

402
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:38,297
<b>Someone interrupted</b>
<b>her while she was typing,</b>

403
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:39,756
<b>and it got autocorrected?</b>

404
00:21:41,842 --> 00:21:44,386
<b>"Pa, just pick me up at the corner.</b>
<b>By the shed over. THERE"</b>

405
00:21:44,469 --> 00:21:45,554
<b>Maybe.</b>

406
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:52,561
<b>[unsettling music playing]</b>

407
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:57,316
<b>Edong.</b>

408
00:21:58,233 --> 00:21:59,234
<b>Where are you?</b>

409
00:22:00,485 --> 00:22:02,237
<b>They're about to bring Crisanto out.</b>

410
00:22:05,073 --> 00:22:06,116
<b>[Edong] </b><i><b>I'm just here.</b></i>

411
00:22:06,199 --> 00:22:11,163
<b>[unsettling music continues]</b>

412
00:22:11,246 --> 00:22:12,414
<b>Where?</b>

413
00:22:13,373 --> 00:22:15,250
<b>You'll see me…</b>

414
00:22:16,918 --> 00:22:18,503
<b>when they bring him out.</b>

415
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:25,594
<b>[unsettling music continues]</b>

416
00:22:36,354 --> 00:22:37,731
<b>Can you see him?</b>

417
00:22:38,356 --> 00:22:40,567
<b>-[exhales deeply]</b>
<b>-[phone chimes]</b>

418
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:44,529
<b>"HE'S HERE ALREADY,</b>
<b>BUT HE REFUSES TO FACE ME"</b>

419
00:22:46,073 --> 00:22:50,452
<b>[unsettling music continues]</b>

420
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:53,121
<b>[phone ringing]</b>

421
00:22:53,830 --> 00:22:55,290
<b>[Erica] </b><i><b>Edong is already in the area,</b></i>

422
00:22:55,373 --> 00:22:57,834
<b>but Lucas isn't</b>
<b>sure of his exact location.</b>

423
00:22:57,918 --> 00:22:58,877
<b>[Locsin] </b><i><b>Copy.</b></i>

424
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:02,547
<b>Positive.</b>

425
00:23:03,090 --> 00:23:09,763
<b>[unsettling music continues]</b>

426
00:23:17,270 --> 00:23:19,564
<b>[music crescendos]</b>

427
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:23,235
<b>"PA, JUST PICK ME UP AT THE CORNER.</b>

428
00:23:23,318 --> 00:23:24,694
<b>BY THE SHED OVER. </b><i><b>THERE</b></i><b>"</b>

429
00:23:27,948 --> 00:23:31,952
<b>[pensive music playing]</b>

430
00:23:32,035 --> 00:23:33,161
<b>Hi, auntie.</b>

431
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:47,467
<b>-[thud]</b>
<b>-[gasps]</b><i><b> Oh, auntie!</b></i>

432
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:48,760
<i><b>Auntie!</b></i>

433
00:23:51,429 --> 00:23:54,599
<i><b>-Auntie. I wish you had called me.</b></i>
<i><b>-There.</b></i>

434
00:23:55,183 --> 00:23:56,268
<i><b>There.</b></i>

435
00:23:56,351 --> 00:23:57,310
<i><b>-There.</b></i>
<i><b>-There?</b></i>

436
00:23:57,936 --> 00:23:59,020
<b>There.</b>

437
00:24:00,981 --> 00:24:01,898
<b>[exhales]</b>

438
00:24:01,982 --> 00:24:09,781
<b>[eerie music playing]</b>

439
00:24:24,087 --> 00:24:31,052
<b>[eerie music continues]</b>

440
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:52,991
<b>[eerie music continues]</b>

441
00:25:07,088 --> 00:25:14,054
<b>[eerie music continues]</b>

442
00:25:19,017 --> 00:25:20,143
<b>[clicks]</b>

443
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:34,407
<b>[eerie music continues]</b>

444
00:25:36,159 --> 00:25:37,118
<b>[gasps]</b>

445
00:25:37,744 --> 00:25:38,912
<b>-[gasps]</b>
<b>-[suitcase slams]</b>

446
00:25:38,995 --> 00:25:45,168
<b>[music becomes dramatic]</b>

447
00:25:45,252 --> 00:25:47,629
<b>[breathes heavily]</b>

448
00:25:50,298 --> 00:25:52,384
<b>[breathes heavily]</b>

449
00:25:53,260 --> 00:25:54,344
<b>[exhales sharply]</b>

450
00:25:54,427 --> 00:26:01,393
<b>[dramatic music continues]</b>

451
00:26:11,695 --> 00:26:18,910
<b>[music becomes tense]</b>

452
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:29,296
<b>[music turns sinister]</b>

453
00:26:34,301 --> 00:26:38,013
<b>[quivered breaths]</b>

454
00:26:39,472 --> 00:26:42,142
<b>[young Alice crying] </b><i><b>Mama!</b></i>

455
00:26:42,225 --> 00:26:43,601
<b>[glass breaks]</b>

456
00:26:45,645 --> 00:26:48,148
<i><b>Just a moment, Alice. I'll just pay this.</b></i>

457
00:26:51,526 --> 00:26:58,658
<b>[sinister music intensifies]</b>

458
00:27:13,548 --> 00:27:16,051
<b>[breathes shakily]</b>

459
00:27:16,134 --> 00:27:23,099
<b>[sinister music continues]</b>

460
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:30,523
<i><b>What am I doing, Mama?</b></i>

461
00:27:30,607 --> 00:27:32,150
<i><b>I have to do this.</b></i>

462
00:27:32,233 --> 00:27:34,986
<i><b>I can't let these demons get away</b></i>

463
00:27:35,070 --> 00:27:37,447
<i><b>without paying for</b></i>
<i><b>everything they did to us.</b></i>

464
00:27:37,530 --> 00:27:38,656
<i><b>Watch me.</b></i>

465
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:40,492
<i><b>-That's Edong!</b></i>
<i><b>-You bastard!</b></i>

466
00:27:40,575 --> 00:27:42,160
<b>-</b><i><b>Edong!</b></i>
<b>-[gunshots]</b>

467
00:27:42,243 --> 00:27:43,912
<b>-[engine revving]</b>
<b>-[police siren wails]</b>

468
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:46,206
<b>[Beth]</b><i><b> Why hasn't Erica</b></i>
<i><b>sent a text or called yet?</b></i>

469
00:27:46,289 --> 00:27:47,749
<i><b>Even Alice.</b></i>
<i><b>She should have been home by now.</b></i>

470
00:27:47,832 --> 00:27:49,542
<i><b>-Where is she?</b></i>
<i><b>-At Uncle Edward's place.</b></i>

471
00:27:50,502 --> 00:27:52,587
<i><b>-It was you.</b></i>
<b>-[young Alice crying]</b>

472
00:27:52,670 --> 00:27:54,798
<i><b>You're a monster! You're a monster!</b></i>

473
00:27:54,881 --> 00:27:55,840
<i><b>Help!</b></i>

474
00:27:55,924 --> 00:27:59,260
<i><b>This is just like that,</b></i>
<i><b>that night Louisa was killed.</b></i>

475
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:01,012
<i><b>-No!</b></i>
<i><b>-Louisa!</b></i>

476
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:02,305
<i><b>Finally…</b></i>

477
00:28:02,389 --> 00:28:04,349
<i><b>it is all complete.</b></i>

478
00:28:04,432 --> 00:28:06,059
<i><b>Who should I start with?</b></i>

479
00:28:06,142 --> 00:28:08,019
<i><b>Edong, forgive us!</b></i>

480
00:28:08,103 --> 00:28:10,814
<i><b>-Please forgive me!</b></i>
<i><b>-You destroyed my family!</b></i>

481
00:28:10,897 --> 00:28:12,107
<b>-[gunshot]</b>
<b>-[screams]</b>
